Ralene is saying something very interesting, but I disagree slightly with her statment.  In my house, between my sister and I (and I too am a girl) she does almost all of the household chores along with my family while I do little to none. I think my family slowly conditioned us kids to be that way while we were growing up and it became obvious to them that I had serious interest, and mediocre talent in film, video, and photography.  While my life took a direct focus and I developed skills of my own, only my sister was left to shoulder the burden of chores. It's scary watching her doing these things around the house because like Ralene I am afraid that my sister will not be able to develop her life outside of the house and become something.
